cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with the design of testing schemes for identifying defective items in a large set, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The construction of disjunct matrices and their relaxed version, almost disjunct matrices, involves combinatorial designs (cs.DM) and error-correcting codes (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the analysis of the average distance of constant weight codes, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
